    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "So I was thinking about this, In React-Instantsearch, every `single` change is  triggered by a `refine`, Would it be possible that multiple `refines` can be clubbed together and made a single query? \r\n\r\nSo basically we will let the users quickly click around and apply the filters and we `debounce` all the refines and combine and make a single query. \r\n\r\nDoes that make sense?  ",
