  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Would it be possible that multiple refines can be clubbed together and made a single query?\r\n\r\nThe issue is that each refine sends a different set of results and allowed filtering options set. Which mean you can't bundle them since they might no more be relevant.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n- refinementList shows sci-fi and romance genres\r\n- click on sci-fi genre\r\n- UI updates, romance is no more selectable\r\n- => if we allowed for bundle, we would show a state that is not relevant/true",
    "created_at": "2017-07-05T15:34:41Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5268#issuecomment-1363064116",
    "id": 1363064116,
    "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5268",
    "node_id": "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDEzNjMwNjQxMTY=",
    "performed_via_github_app": null,
    "pin": null,
    "reactions": {
      "+1": 2,
      "-1": 0,
      "confused": 0,
